ill prevent other      \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mtasks from running until it completes. This can be a problem in production code, where responsiveness and    \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mconcurrency are crucial.                                                                                     \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mLong Function\u001b[0m: Although the functions are relatively short, the \u001b[1;36;40mshow_memory\u001b[0m function can be considered a     \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mlong function because it performs multiple tasks: retrieving memory information and printing it.             \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mLack of Error Handling\u001b[0m: The code does not handle potential errors that may occur when retrieving memory      \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0minformation.                                                                                                 \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                 \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1mImprovements\u001b[0m                                                                                                    \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                 \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mAsync Endpoint\u001b[0m: To avoid blocking operations, we can create an async endpoint using a framework like FastAPI \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mor Flask. This will allow the function to run asynchronously, improving responsiveness and concurrency.      \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mSeparate Concerns\u001b[0m: We can separate the concerns of retrieving memory information and printing it into two    \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mseparate functions. This will make the code more modular and easier to maintain.                             \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m 3 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mError Handling\u001b[0m: We can add try-except blocks to handle potential errors that may occur when retrieving       \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mmemory information.                                                                                          \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                 \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1mProduction Suggestions\u001b[0m                                                                                          \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m                                                                                                                 \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m 1 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mUse a Framework\u001b[0m: Use a framework like FastAPI or Flask to create an async endpoint for retrieving memory     \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0minformation.                                                                                                 \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m 2 \u001b[0m\u001b[1mImplement Error Handling\u001b[0m: Implement try-except blocks to handle potential errors that may occur when         \u001b[33m│\u001b[0m\n","\u001b[33m│\u001b[0m \u001b[36m   \u001b[0mretrieving memory information.                                                                               \u001b[33m│